description: A woman eats cashews and almonds to get her calorie and protein intake. A serving of almonds contains \param{CaloriesAlmonds} calories and \param{ProteinAlmonds} grams of protein. A serving of cashews contains \param{CaloriesCashews} calories and \param{ProteinCashews} grams of protein. The woman decides to eat at least twice as many servings of almonds as cashews. Furthermore, a serving of almonds contains \param{FatAlmonds} grams of fat while a serving of cashews contains \param{FatCashews} grams of fat. If the woman needs to consume at least \param{MinCalories} calories and \param{MinProtein} grams of protein this week, how many servings of each should she eat to minimize her fat intake?
